        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 3:39AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 338 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms just west of the Irion and Sterling County
lines. Movement was east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sterling City, Silver, Broome, Arden, Barnhart, Mertzon, Us-
87 Near The Coke-Tom Green County Line, Water Valley, and Sherwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
